+# Hyperclaw Project Handoff
+
+**Last updated**: 2026-02-20  
+**Repo**: https://github.com/MikeHLee/hyperclaw (private fork of openclaw/openclaw)
+
+---
+
+## Project Summary
+
+Hyperclaw is a security-hardened fork of [OpenClaw](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw) designed to run AI agents in Docker with:
+
+1. **Human-in-the-loop approval** for all shell commands and browser navigation via Telegram
+2. **Full session logging** for auditing and training data
+3. **Attack detection & logging** inspired by the panasonic `chat_api` `report_user` pattern
+4. **Encrypted local secrets vault** that never exposes secrets to the model
+5. **Prompt injection defense** via system prompt hardening + model self-reporting tools
+
+---
+
+## What Was Built
+
+### Core Patches (1 file modified, 1 new)
+
+| File | Purpose |
+|------|---------|
+| `src/infra/browser-approvals.ts` | URL allowlist (read/write `browser-approvals.json`, hostname/glob/prefix matching) |
+| `src/agents/tools/browser-tool.ts` | Navigate gate — checks allowlist, calls `exec.approval.request`, handles allow-once/allow-always/deny |
+
+### Plugin: `extensions/hyperclaw-security/`
+
+| File | Purpose |
+|------|---------|
+| `index.ts` | Plugin entry — wires all modules |
+| `src/history-logger.ts` | JSONL session log → `~/.openclaw/logs/history/YYYY/MM/DD/` |
+| `src/attack-logger.ts` | Incident log → `~/.openclaw/logs/attacks/` + Telegram alert |
+| `src/telegram.ts` | Minimal Telegram Bot API client |
+| `src/secrets-store.ts` | AES-256-GCM vault, PBKDF2 key derived from gateway token |
+| `src/tools/report-injection.ts` | `report_injection` tool (model self-reports attacks) |
+| `src/tools/deposit-secret.ts` | `deposit_secret` — injects vault secret into browser field |
+| `src/hooks/secrets-redact.ts` | `tool_result_persist` hook — strips secret values before history write |
+
+### Security Configuration (new files)
+
+| File | Purpose |
+|------|---------|
+| `docker-compose.secure.yml` | Hardened compose: read_only, cap_drop ALL, no_new_privileges, resource limits |
+| `.env.secure.example` | Secure env template with required tokens |
+| `config/exec-approvals.json.example` | Deny-by-default exec policy |
+| `config/browser-approvals.json.example` | Deny-by-default browser policy |
+| `config/openclaw.json.example` | Full config with Telegram approval forwarding + plugin setup |
+
+---
+
+## Current Branch State
