+
+## Setup Instructions
+
+### 1. Create config directory
+
+```bash
+mkdir -p ~/.hyperclaw/{workspace,logs/history,logs/attacks,state/secrets}
+chmod 700 ~/.hyperclaw
+```
+
+### 2. Copy config files
+
+```bash
+cd /Users/Michaellee/Documents/Runes/hyperclaw
+cp .env.secure.example ~/.hyperclaw/.env
+cp config/openclaw.json.example ~/.hyperclaw/openclaw.json
+cp config/exec-approvals.json.example ~/.hyperclaw/exec-approvals.json
+cp config/browser-approvals.json.example ~/.hyperclaw/browser-approvals.json
+chmod 600 ~/.hyperclaw/.env
+```
+
+### 3. Generate gateway token and fill in .env
+
+```bash
+# Generate secure token
+openssl rand -hex 32
+
+# Edit ~/.hyperclaw/.env and fill in:
+#   HYPERCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=<generated token>
+#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=<your key>
+#   TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=<from @BotFather>
+#   TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=<your chat id from @userinfobot>
+```
+
+### 4. Update openclaw.json with your values
+
+Replace `${TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID}` and `${TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}` placeholders with actual values.
+
+### 5. Build Docker image
+
+```bash
+docker build -t hyperclaw:local \
+  --build-arg OPENCLAW_INSTALL_BROWSER=1 \
+  .
+```
+
+### 6. Start gateway
+
+```bash
+docker compose -f docker-compose.secure.yml up -d
+```
+
+### 7. Verify
+
+```bash
+# Check logs
+docker logs hyperclaw-gateway
+
+# Test health
+curl http://127.0.0.1:18789/health
+```
+
